{
  "texts": [
    "Active silicon participants produced significantly fewer quotes about negative beliefs about capability than sedentary silicon participants.",
    "Active silicon participants also produce significantly fewer negative beliefs about environmental barriers to physical activity than sedentary silicon participants (Fig 5).",
    "Backward continuity indicates that the backstory of silicon participants can be inferred from their responses.",
    "We found that Backward continuity was satisfied because we could easily identify the backstories from LLM-generated responses.",
    "That is, we could identify which silicon participants were male versus female, what comorbid conditions they had, whether they lived in a city or not, and whether they were physically active."
  ]
}